21/06/2004
LEFKOSA, Cyprus -- Prime Minister Mehmet Ali Talat of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" said Sunday (20 June) that his government is preparing to integrate with the European community and the world, once isolation of his part of the island ends.
Talat, presenting a review of the work of the EU Co-ordination Committee, said the committee would continue its efforts until the end of next month.
In other news, Turkey's ruling Justice and Development Party is holding a national policy symposium in Ankara on the EU adjustment process.
The symposium weighs the advantages and disadvantages of social policies aimed at facilitating Turkey's accession to the EU.
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 20/06/04)
